The paper proposes a novel approach for unsupervised representation learning using Convolutional Self-Organizing Neural Networks (CSNNs) that combines Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs), clustering via Self-Organizing Maps (SOMs), and Hebbian Learning. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks such as Cifar10, Cifar100, Tiny ImageNet, and ImageNet, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of clustering and Hebbian Learning also suggests that the paper may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a Backpropagation-free approach, which may also suggest that it belongs to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-categories.
